  "description": "<em>Virtua Racing</em> is  Sega's first ever 3D, polygon-based racing game. The game consists of racing Formula-1-looking cars around a beginner, intermediate, or expert track, competing against a second player or computer drivers. Despite having Formula-1 cars, the game controls are very &quot;arcadey&quot; and players can see the leap they made from here to Daytona.<br><br>The Megadrive/Genesis version of <em>Virtua Racing</em> is of note as it is the only game for the system which features the SVP chip (Sega Virtua Processor). The chip is a 3D processor built into each cartridge (the console itself had limited 3D capability) and is very similar to the SNES's SuperFX chips, used in games such as <em>Starfox</em> and <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/stunt-race-fx\">Stunt Race FX</a>.",
